# Backend Migrations

Alembic migrations live here.

Initialize with: alembic init migrations
Run with:        alembic upgrade head

Cloud SQL app-role grants:

- Script: `infra/sql/grant_app_role.sql`
- Run the script as a privileged/admin DB role in the target database.
- Replace `app_role_here` in that script with the DB role used by `DATABASE_URL`.

Example apply command (adjust host/db/user/script path):

- `psql "host=<host> dbname=<db> user=<admin_user> sslmode=require" -f infra/sql/grant_app_role.sql`

Post-apply smoke checks (authenticated):

- `GET /api/folders` returns `200`.
- `GET /api/conversations` returns `200`.
- Repeat both requests multiple times; no `users_firebase_uid_key` duplicate errors.

Vertex embedding migration (1024 -> 768):

- Script: `infra/sql/002_vertex_vector_768_migration.sql`
- This script drops vector indexes, clears old vectors, alters both vector columns to `vector(768)`, and recreates indexes.
- Apply as a privileged/admin DB role:
  - `psql "host=<host> dbname=<db> user=<admin_user> sslmode=require" -f infra/sql/002_vertex_vector_768_migration.sql`
- After apply, reindex documents so fresh 768-d embeddings are written.

Summary enrichment + OCR provenance:

- Script: `infra/sql/004_summary_and_ocr_metadata.sql`
- Adds `documents.entities` (jsonb), `documents.subtype` (text), and `chunks.source_type` (text).
- All columns are nullable and default to safe values — no backfill required.
- After apply, newly indexed documents will carry richer summary metadata and
  OCR-page chunks will be tagged so the UI / retrieval can treat them specially.
